title: Bill Elgart-A Life; audiophile CD, Mark Levinson, EAC FLAC
description:
This recording was originally made by Mark Levinson on 1-inch 30 ips tape. It was transferred to CD by Bob Ludwig at Masterdisk. 

It is simply one man and his percussion set, simply miked and obviously without limitation-so beware and don't turn it up too much during the softer bits or you may well blow drivers. 

Not everyone will like this 'content'...but it is one of the very best examples how good 16/44 digital audio can be.
